    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.8.0-dev+11-gd3121f1e6-dirty\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ncouldn't check\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nGentoo\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.25.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nGentoo Repository\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nVery sporadically, after I edited a file and `:wq` it. I shut down the laptop. When I turn it back on the content of the file is missing. This has happened to me 2/3 times a month but it's extremely annoying\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe file content still there\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nAll the content missing",
